"{\"uid\": \"nbcolympics.com-post-297461\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"All eyes were on the United States'CJ Nickolasheading into the 2024 Olympic taekwondo competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 98, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top American in a deep Olympic field, Nickolas hoped to win the United States' first gold medal in men's taekwondo since 2004.\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 168, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999929376385083, \"rank\": 6.854939392929739e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the 23-year-old missed the podium in Paris.\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.102613097302158e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other top stories in Paris included the hometown run of France'sAlthea Laurinin the women's heavyweight class and 18-year old AmericanKristina Teachoutclaiming women's welterweight bronze.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.102613097302158e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a look at those top moments that made taekwondo in 2024 an event to remember.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RESULTS: TaekwondoREPLAYS: Taekwondo    Tunisia'sFiras Katoussiwon the gold medal in the men's welterweight division after defeatingMehran Barkhordariof Iran in the gold medal bout.\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999768897010848, \"rank\": 2.3108545255558284e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nickolas lost to Katoussi in the semifinals after a kick to the body in the bout's final seconds.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nickloas kept the pressure on Katoussi but did not connect with enough significant shots when it mattered most.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Alessiothen defeated Nickolas in a bronze medal bout to end the American's podium dreams.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999935088001, \"rank\": 5.287151957735777e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nickolas attempted to wow the crowd with his flashy style, however he fell short against the Italian.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1139, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9967886788210102, \"rank\": 0.0030815090339370186, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put the raw version of myself out there for everybody to see.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was a massive risk and I failed,\\\" Nickolas said.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I gotta do some soul searching to figure out what that means.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[People] do not want to just see crazy kicks.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They want to see me win.\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I need to figure out how I win.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How do I turn these into wins?\\\"\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FULL REPLAY: Men's 80kg Finals  Medalists (Men's 80kg)Gold:Firas Katoussi (Tunisia)Silver:Mehran Barkhordari (Iran)Bronze:Simone Alessio (Italy)Bronze:Edi Hrnic (Denmark)  Laurin won France's first taekwondo gold in front of an electric crowd at the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzuki_Alto\", \"score\": 0.9999979217681124, \"rank\": 1.8042382959070562e-06, \"text\": \"Mehran\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzuki_Alto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzuki_Alto\"}, {\"begin\": 1595, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\", \"score\": 0.999980120190021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Alessio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\"}, {\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9870816077118509, \"rank\": 0.010971668872492367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old took the victory at the last moment with a dynamic kick to the head to make history for the French.\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1846, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6738670150909717, \"rank\": 0.4799714855256705, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very happy to have won my first Olympic gold medal...\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just incredible what's happening tonight, especially in Paris in front of the French public,\\\" Laurin told reporters.\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.102613097302158e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6738670150909717, \"rank\": 0.4799714855256705, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was very intense to hear all the people...\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not necessarily used to that, so discovering the atmosphere was quite something and in the end I got used to it really well.\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I acclimatized like crazy,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laurin won a bronze in Tokyo, showing immense improvement in Paris en route to a heart-warming hometown win.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999547355572869, \"rank\": 4.526649134454264e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.102613097302158e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FULL REPLAY: Women's 67+kg Finals  Medalists (Women's 67+kg)Gold:Althea Laurin (France)Silver:Svetlana Osipova (Uzbekistan)Bronze:Lee Da-Bin (South Korea)Bronze:Nafia Kus (T\\u00fcrkiye)  Teachout won the lone American taekwondo medal in Paris, claiming a bronze in the women's 67kg class.\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2429, \"end\": 2435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Flynt\", \"score\": 0.8997071470265992, \"rank\": 0.11104805299808906, \"text\": \"Althea\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Flynt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Flynt\"}, {\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dietrich_von_Bern\", \"score\": 0.9999999946098796, \"rank\": 5.389941273862812e-09, \"text\": \"Laurin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dietrich_von_Bern\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dietrich_von_Bern\"}, {\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetlana_Osipova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Svetlana Osipova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetlana_Osipova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetlana_Osipova\"}, {\"begin\": 2536, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.090276538629577e-23, \"text\": \"T\\u00fcrkiye\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 2568, \"end\": 2576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999935088001, \"rank\": 5.287151957735777e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2596, \"end\": 2601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.102613097302158e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 18-year-old defeated China'sSong Jiein the bronze medal bout, contributing to the United States' Olympics-high 126 total medals.\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2735, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999929376385083, \"rank\": 6.854939392929739e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teachout discussed her journey to the Olympics, qualifying for the Paris Games and taking home a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had a hamstring injury in my first year as a senior, and that took me out of a lot of big competitions that would have set me up to have an easier qualification.\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I have always had the harder route in sports,\\\" Teachout said.\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And even getting this fricking bronze.\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't the best, it was the hardest route to get a medal.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having to go through the motions of losing and, you know, get it back together and fight.\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So yeah, it's been an emotional journey.\\\"\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FULL REPLAY: Women's 67kg  Medalists (Women's 67kg)Gold:Viviana Marton (Hungary)Silver:Aleksandra Perisic (Serbia)Bronze:Kristina Teachout (United States)Bronze:Sarah Chaari (Belgium)  Note: Some components ofNBCOlympics.commay not be optimized for users browsing with           Internet           Explorer 11, 10 or older browsers or systems.\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3416, \"end\": 3423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viviana_(TV_series)\", \"score\": 0.6955965431961727, \"rank\": 0.2500000000000275, \"text\": \"Viviana\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viviana_(TV_series)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viviana_(TV_series)\"}, {\"begin\": 3424, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marton,_New_Zealand\", \"score\": 0.8494807876253228, \"rank\": 0.09385219097447657, \"text\": \"Marton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marton,_New_Zealand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marton,_New_Zealand\"}, {\"begin\": 3481, \"end\": 3489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristina_Keneally\", \"score\": 0.9988794802025133, \"rank\": 0.001121776770429903, \"text\": \"Kristina\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbp